"A modern test management web application built with React.js featuring comprehensive project, test case, and defect tracking capabilities. The application uses Context API for global state management with mock data architecture, enabling real-time UI updates without page refresh. Core features include user authentication via login page with first/last name fields, a dashboard with three-tab navigation (Projects, Defect Tracker, Testing Overview), full CRUD operations for projects with statistics cards, detailed test case management with forms and table views, and complete defect lifecycle tracking with filtering capabilities. The design emphasizes a modern professional aesthetic with clean card-based layouts, status-driven color coding (green for passed/resolved, red for failed/critical, yellow for in-progress, grey for pending), smooth transitions, and responsive layouts optimized for desktop with mobile compatibility. Technical implementation leverages react-router-dom for navigation, react-hook-form for form handling, framer-motion for animations, lucide-react for icons, and react-hot-toast for notifications. Reusable components include Modal and ConfirmDialog for consistent user interactions. The application provides intuitive UX with proper loading states, success feedback, scrollable modals, and interactive hover effects with subtle shadows and gradients for visual depth.\\n\\n**Last changes**: Initial project setup with complete file structure including authentication, dashboard navigation, project management, test case handling, defect tracking, and global state management using Context API with mock data."